- What?

24:35.839 --> 24:37.972
- Nice job, Bart.
- You haven't heard yet?

24:37.974 --> 24:39.808
I gotta say,
I'm a little jealous.

24:39.810 --> 24:42.709
What're you t...
what're you talking about?

24:42.711 --> 24:44.714
- Congratulations!
- No, no, no, no. Okay.

24:52.555 --> 24:54.057
How excited are you?

24:57.794 --> 24:58.963
Miss Fincher!

25:01.765 --> 25:04.965
Unh-unh. No.
What're you trying to do to me?

25:04.967 --> 25:07.936
I can't do this.
I didn't even try out.

25:07.938 --> 25:09.971
You can. And you will.

25:09.973 --> 25:12.005
And there'll be no further
discussion about it.

25:12.007 --> 25:14.576
No, no, no, no, no.
Look, I'm a Millard.

25:14.578 --> 25:16.844
Okay, you don't understand.
Millards play football.

25:16.846 --> 25:19.781
- Millards do not sing.
- You have a gift, Bart.

25:19.783 --> 25:22.716
And in my class,
you will be required to use it.

25:22.718 --> 25:24.819
Or fail. It's your choice.

25:24.821 --> 25:26.855
Look, my leg is still in a cast.
I can't even walk.

25:26.857 --> 25:28.889
There's two months
until the production.

25:28.891 --> 25:31.559
You have plenty of time to heal.
Please stop making excuses.

25:31.561 --> 25:33.962
Okay, I don't sing like that.
That Broadway stuff.

25:33.964 --> 25:35.597
I'll teach you.

25:35.599 --> 25:37.698
Look, Miss Fincher,
I like you, okay?

25:37.700 --> 25:39.701
You seem like
a real good person.

25:39.703 --> 25:43.905
I respect you,
but there is no way, ever,

25:43.907 --> 25:49.142
at all, ever that you are
gonna get me on that stage.

25:49.144 --> 25:51.014
Mm-hmm.

25:52.815 --> 25:55.716
<i>♪ There's
a bright golden haze ♪</i>

25:55.718 --> 25:58.253
<i>♪ On the meadow ♪</i>

25:58.255 --> 26:00.855
<i>♪ There's
a bright golden haze ♪</i>

26:00.857 --> 26:03.957
<i>♪ On the meadow ♪</i>

26:03.959 --> 26:06.194
<i>♪ The corn is as high ♪</i>

26:06.196 --> 26:11.032
<i>♪ As an elephant's eye ♪</i>

26:11.034 --> 26:13.635
<i>♪ And it looks like
it's climbing ♪</i>

26:13.637 --> 26:17.972
<i>♪ Clear up to the sky ♪</i>

26:17.974 --> 26:23.844
<i>♪ Oh,
what a beautiful mornin' ♪</i>

26:23.846 --> 26:29.583
<i>♪ Oh,
what a beautiful day ♪</i>

26:29.585 --> 26:32.619
<i>♪ I've got
a beautiful feelin'... ♪</i>

26:32.621 --> 26:35.322
Mercy me,
that can't be his real voice.

26:35.324 --> 26:36.890
Yeah, it is.

26:36.892 --> 26:39.596
<i>♪ ...goin' my way ♪</i>

26:42.064 --> 26:45.132
Well,
punch a monkey's uncle.

26:45.134 --> 26:47.668
<i>♪ All the sounds
of the earth ♪</i>

26:47.670 --> 26:50.671
<i>♪ Are like music ♪</i>

26:50.673 --> 26:53.174
<i>♪ All the sounds
of the earth ♪</i>

26:53.176 --> 26:55.342
<i>♪ Are like music ♪</i>

26:55.344 --> 26:58.980
<i>♪ 'The breeze is so busy ♪</i>

26:58.982 --> 27:02.617
<i>♪ It don't miss a tree ♪</i>

27:02.619 --> 27:05.919
<i>♪ An' that ol' weepin' willer ♪</i>

27:05.921 --> 27:10.692
<i>♪ Is laughin' at me ♪</i>

27:10.694 --> 27:16.598
<i>♪ Oh,
what a beautiful mornin' ♪</i>

27:16.600 --> 27:21.769
<i>♪ Oh,
what a beautiful day ♪</i>

27:21.771 --> 27:27.708
<i>♪ I've got
a beautiful feelin' ♪</i>

27:27.710 --> 27:33.747
<i>♪ Everything's goin' my way ♪</i>

27:33.749 --> 27:39.721
<i>♪ Oh,
what a beautiful ♪</i>

27:39.723 --> 27:45.696
<i>♪ Da-a-y ♪</i>

27:51.368 --> 27:52.570
Whoo!

28:09.753 --> 28:13.286
Sir, you need to understand.
It's hospital policy.

28:13.288 --> 28:16.090
Well, you can't keep me here.
I'm free to go.

28:16.092 --> 28:18.892
No, you're not.

28:18.894 --> 28:20.661
We saw something
in your blood work

28:20.663 --> 28:22.763
that concerned us,
so we ran a few tests.

28:22.765 --> 28:24.765
And I'd like to discuss
the results with you.

28:24.767 --> 28:26.967
You got my number.
You can call me.

28:26.969 --> 28:29.670
We need to have
this conversation now.

28:29.672 --> 28:31.007
Okay.

28:34.777 --> 28:36.310
Why did I black out?

28:36.312 --> 28:39.080
Because of extremely
low blood sugar.

28:39.082 --> 28:43.184
So you're saying, what?
I'm diabetic?

28:43.186 --> 28:44.785
No.

28:44.787 --> 28:47.355
On your MRI,
we discovered a mass.

28:47.357 --> 28:49.857
- We believe it's cancer.
- No.

28:49.859 --> 28:53.261
No. No, I don't...

28:53.263 --> 28:55.263
We'd like to run
a few more tests

28:55.265 --> 28:57.400
and then decide on the best
treatment options for you.

28:59.436 --> 29:02.302
I don't...
I don't need your treatment.

29:02.304 --> 29:04.741
I'm gonna go home.

29:07.475 --> 29:09.910
Mr. Millard,
if you refuse treatment,

29:09.912 --> 29:11.814
it could drastically reduce
your chances.

29:22.825 --> 29:25.827
Dad. What happened?

29:25.829 --> 29:29.097
Oh, I'm fine.
I'm just fine.

29:29.099 --> 29:30.831
Okay, well,
let me drive you home.

29:30.833 --> 29:32.332
I-I can make it myself.

29:32.334 --> 29:35.837
Mr. Millard, are you okay?

29:35.839 --> 29:38.205
I'm Shannon,
Bart's girlfriend?

29:38.207 --> 29:41.175
Oh, hello, Shannon.

29:41.177 --> 29:44.846
How'd Bart wind up
with someone as pretty as you?

29:44.848 --> 29:46.313
Thank you.

29:46.315 --> 29:48.849
I'm fine.
I'm gonna be all right.

29:48.851 --> 29:50.483
But did they say what's wrong?

29:50.485 --> 29:52.153
Uh, I just had
a little incident.

29:52.155 --> 29:53.920
I had low blood sugar.

29:53.922 --> 29:57.358
I was over at the diner,
and... and I fell down.

29:57.360 --> 30:00.895
And actually,
I was looking at your name

30:00.897 --> 30:04.899
on an advertisement
for a play.

30:05.301 --> 30:07.838
Didn't think
you'd wanna come.

30:09.505 --> 30:13.507
Did he ever sing for you?
'Cause I-I had no idea.

30:13.509 --> 30:15.176
I had no idea at all.

30:15.178 --> 30:16.878
He was good.
He was real good.

30:16.880 --> 30:18.879
I'm sorry, Dad.
I should've invited you.

30:18.881 --> 30:21.415
Oh, don't... we'll talk
about it later, son.

30:21.417 --> 30:23.050
- Just let me drive you home.
- Oh, no.

30:23.052 --> 30:26.320
You take care
of your pretty girl there.

30:26.322 --> 30:30.558
Where're you going?

30:30.560 --> 30:33.864
Going to the cast party.
I'm not missing it for this.

30:36.431 --> 30:40.134
Excuse me. I'm sorry.
What's wrong with him?

30:40.136 --> 30:42.136
- Are you family?
- No.

30:42.138 --> 30:44.504
Well, you need to ask him.

30:44.506 --> 30:45.939
Thank you.

31:03.059 --> 31:04.926
You're up early.

31:04.928 --> 31:07.594
Made my son breakfast.

31:07.596 --> 31:10.430
What's with the getup?
Going to a funeral?

31:10.432 --> 31:13.533
No.
Just going to church, Dad.

31:13.535 --> 31:15.037
Church.

31:18.207 --> 31:19.810
Sit down and eat.

31:22.211 --> 31:26.112
C'mon, sit down and eat.
Getting cold.

31:26.114 --> 31:30.618
Hey'd you see this?
Did you see that?

31:30.620 --> 31:35.156
Look at that.
Front page.

31:35.158 --> 31:37.390
You look like
a Pinocchio cowboy.

31:37.392 --> 31:41.028
It's a good joke.

31:41.030 --> 31:43.930
So that's what I am to you,
a joke?

31:43.932 --> 31:44.965
I didn't say that.

31:44.967 --> 31:46.399
You just said it.

31:46.401 --> 31:48.069
Don't put words in my mouth.

31:48.071 --> 31:51.205
What if I wanna sing?
Why's that so funny?

31:51.207 --> 31:53.073
I mean, maybe I'm good at it.

31:53.075 --> 31:56.109
The pastor of the church
asked me to sing this morning.

31:56.111 --> 31:57.544
It's gotta mean something.

31:57.546 --> 31:59.613
He ask you to sing
for a living?

31:59.615 --> 32:01.514
That's what I'm saying.

32:01.516 --> 32:03.551
You're gonna need to find
something you're good at

32:03.553 --> 32:05.319
that you can actually earn
a living at

32:05.321 --> 32:07.120
'cause you're gonna have
to support yourself

32:07.122 --> 32:08.656
- one of these days.
- How do you even know?

32:08.658 --> 32:10.992
You've never
even heard me sing.

32:10.994 --> 32:12.659
Well, that's not my fault.

32:12.661 --> 32:15.362
All I hear out of you
is whining and moaning.

32:15.364 --> 32:19.466
Okay. I'm singing
this morning at church.

32:19.468 --> 32:21.636
10:00 on radio AM 1080.

32:21.638 --> 32:23.670
- Why don't you come watch me sing?
- No, I can't do that.

32:23.672 --> 32:25.673
- Why not?
- No. I just don't belong there.

32:25.675 --> 32:28.011
- Why?
- I just don't. I don't!

32:30.013 --> 32:31.946
Don't belong there.

32:31.948 --> 32:33.150
Okay.

32:39.455 --> 32:41.254
My boy Bart's, oh,

32:41.256 --> 32:43.224
he's nothin'
but a big disappointment.

32:43.226 --> 32:46.060
I wish he'd never been born.
Everything'd been just fine.

32:46.062 --> 32:48.161
- Hey...
- All my problems are because of Bart.

32:48.163 --> 32:49.562
Hey, hey,
you put words in my mouth.

32:49.564 --> 32:51.131
I'm gonna put a fist
in your face.

32:51.133 --> 32:52.966
Yeah, I'm a little big
for that, Dad.

32:52.968 --> 32:54.502
- You think?
- I think those days are over.

32:54.504 --> 32:56.436
- Is that what you think?
- Yeah! I do, yeah!

32:56.438 --> 32:58.305
Listen, you have
to talk to me with respect.

32:58.307 --> 33:00.374
I'm the one that puts
the food on the table.

33:00.376 --> 33:02.510
I earn the living around here,
and I'm the one who stayed.

33:02.512 --> 33:04.278
I don't see your Momma
anywhere.

33:04.280 --> 33:06.013
Yeah, well, nobody blames
her for leaving, Dad!

33:06.015 --> 33:07.015
I would've left, too!

33:10.253 --> 33:12.386
Just shut up.
Just shut up and eat.

33:12.388 --> 33:14.088
- I'm not hungry.
- Eat your food.

33:14.090 --> 33:15.391
I'm not hungry!

33:19.294 --> 33:20.964
All right, then.

33:28.004 --> 33:32.173
You kidding me?!
Stay away from me!

33:32.175 --> 33:34.473
I'm serious!
Don't touch me!

33:34.475 --> 33:38.415
I'm done with you! You're crazy!
Get away from me!

34:17.351 --> 34:18.585
Bart, what happened
to your head?

34:18.588 --> 34:20.420
It's bleeding.

34:20.422 --> 34:22.188
- Oh, it's nothing, it's fine.
- Are you okay?

34:22.190 --> 34:23.627
- Are you sure?
- I'm fine

34:25.793 --> 34:27.460
I'm wondering
if you guys could all

34:27.463 --> 34:29.362
maybe pray
for a friend of mine?

34:29.364 --> 34:33.367
This friend I think is lying
to me about their life.

34:33.369 --> 34:35.668
I don't know what to do
because I wanna help,

34:35.670 --> 34:37.737
and they just won't let me,
and I just feel like

34:37.739 --> 34:41.474
the more I try,
it kind of gets worse and worse.

34:41.476 --> 34:45.114
And so now when I look at them,
all I see is a mask.

34:46.416 --> 34:48.547
Pray for them.

34:48.550 --> 34:52.418
No one can live a lie forever,
okay?

34:52.420 --> 34:54.187
Okay, thanks.

34:54.188 --> 34:55.822
Course they know
you're talking about me.

34:55.824 --> 34:57.591
Do you know how embarrassing
that is?

34:57.593 --> 34:59.727
I was just trying
to get you to listen!

34:59.729 --> 35:01.327
What is going on with you?!

35:01.329 --> 35:04.164
- I'm fine.
- You're not fine!

35:04.166 --> 35:06.133
Is it your dad?
I could help.

35:06.135 --> 35:09.102
- Just let me come over.
- I don't want you at my house.

35:09.104 --> 35:11.305
- Why?
- 'Cause I just don't.

35:11.307 --> 35:13.106
Where is this coming from?

35:13.108 --> 35:15.108
I don't know, maybe from deep
inside my mask.

35:15.110 --> 35:16.811
- That's not funny.
- It's kinda funny.

35:16.813 --> 35:18.611
- Please, don't do this.
- You got me all figured out.

35:18.613 --> 35:21.215
You push everyone away!
Don't add me to that list.

35:21.217 --> 35:22.716
I love you.
I've always loved you!

35:22.718 --> 35:24.588
Yeah, well,
I've never really loved you.

35:27.155 --> 35:29.189
I mean, we're...
we're graduating soon.

35:29.191 --> 35:31.191
You're going off to college.
I'm chasing some stupid dream.

35:31.193 --> 35:33.260
- Right?
- I never said your dream was stupid.

35:33.262 --> 35:35.329
I mean, this has been fun.
No regrets for me, all right?

35:35.331 --> 35:36.830
But people change,
you know what I mean?

35:36.832 --> 35:38.765
We obviously can't
get along anymore.

35:38.767 --> 35:42.706
I'm leaving, Shannon.
After graduation I'm... I'm gone.

35:48.677 --> 35:50.711
Please don't.

35:50.713 --> 35:53.446
What?

35:53.448 --> 35:55.548
Go.

35:55.550 --> 35:57.586
I can't stay here,
Shannon.

36:25.814 --> 36:28.249
You know, Mike,
it's amazing how people quit

36:28.251 --> 36:31.251
- when they don't get paid.
- Look, we are opening

36:31.253 --> 36:33.720
for the opening act
at a youth conference.

36:33.722 --> 36:35.923
It's impossible,
that's the whole problem.

36:35.925 --> 36:38.658
"Whether you think you can
or you think you can't,

36:38.660 --> 36:40.727
you're right"...
that's Confucius.

36:40.729 --> 36:42.428
I don't even know
what that means.

36:42.430 --> 36:44.231
And it's offensive to me
as an artist.

36:44.233 --> 36:46.332
An artist?
We're making 90 bucks!

36:46.334 --> 36:47.734
- Right.
- Between the three of us.

36:47.736 --> 36:49.736
We have no vocals.
We got no show.

36:49.738 --> 36:51.671
It's impossible.

36:51.673 --> 36:53.774
Yeah, well,
the only impossible things

36:53.776 --> 36:55.508
are the things
that we call impossible.

36:55.510 --> 36:56.943
What is that? Aristotle?

36:56.945 --> 36:59.613
No,
that one's a fortune cookie.

36:59.615 --> 37:02.249
Nathan,
nobody understands you, man!

37:02.251 --> 37:03.816
- Hey, guys.
- You're always so cranky, man.

37:03.818 --> 37:05.419
- Yeah, since Des Moines.
- Oh, Des Moines.

37:05.421 --> 37:07.320
Why bring up
Des Moines again?

37:07.322 --> 37:09.722
Hey, guys, if you guys
need a singer, I'll sing.

37:09.724 --> 37:12.825
I'm, uh...
I also patch cables,

37:12.827 --> 37:14.827
and, you know,
I can run the board,

37:14.829 --> 37:20.300
and turn the lights on,
and I write songs, too.

37:20.302 --> 37:21.570
Kind of. Sometimes.

37:23.972 --> 37:25.307
Who are you?

37:27.809 --> 37:30.211
<i>I joined up with the band.</i>

37:30.213 --> 37:32.613
<i>All we had was the clothes
on our backs.</i>

37:32.615 --> 37:34.381
<i>Took every gig we could</i>

37:34.383 --> 37:36.283
<i>and anywhere
they'd let us play.</i>

37:36.285 --> 37:38.452
<i>We were all technically
homeless, I guess.</i>

37:44.593 --> 37:47.227
<i>♪ When you can't find
what you're looking for ♪</i>

37:47.229 --> 37:49.396
<i>♪ And your heart's been
screaming for more and more ♪</i>

37:49.398 --> 37:51.398
<i>♪ When you search so
long, you can't even stand ♪</i>

37:51.400 --> 37:54.001
<i>♪ And the way back home
is the Father's hand ♪</i>

37:54.003 --> 37:56.269
<i>♪ Your heart says yes,
your head says more ♪</i>

37:56.271 --> 37:58.338
<i>♪ And in between
is where you're torn ♪</i>

37:58.340 --> 38:00.506
<i>♪ Trace your steps
to where you were ♪</i>

38:00.508 --> 38:06.347
<i>♪ Befo-o-re ♪</i>

38:06.349 --> 38:08.852
<i>♪ Ohh ♪</i>

38:12.021 --> 38:14.224
<i>♪ Trace your steps, now ♪</i>

38:16.525 --> 38:20.260
<i>♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

38:20.262 --> 38:22.494
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

38:22.496 --> 38:25.332
<i>♪ Ooh, whoa, yeah ♪</i>

38:25.334 --> 38:28.401
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

38:31.374 --> 38:32.872
Whoo!

38:32.874 --> 38:35.276
Give it up for Mike
on the guitar!

38:35.278 --> 38:37.044
Yeah!

38:37.046 --> 38:42.048
Mr. Nathan on the bass!
Give it up for Nathan!

38:42.050 --> 38:45.419
Jim on the keys!

38:45.421 --> 38:47.387
- Yeah!
- Yeah, and I'm Bart.

38:47.389 --> 38:49.823
And we are Mercy...

38:49.825 --> 38:53.394
And Robbie on the drums!

38:55.597 --> 38:57.398
He's new.

38:57.400 --> 38:59.399
Thank you all
for being here tonight.

38:59.401 --> 39:00.834
Y'all have a good time?

39:00.836 --> 39:03.003
Yeah!

39:03.005 --> 39:06.709
I sure hope so 'cause
that's all the songs we got.

39:09.412 --> 39:12.412
Encore!

39:12.414 --> 39:13.881
You know what?

39:13.883 --> 39:15.582
Let me tell you a story
before we go.

39:15.584 --> 39:20.086
Um... 'cause when I was, uh...

39:20.088 --> 39:23.890
ten, 11 years old,
life was tough.

39:23.892 --> 39:26.727
I mean, it...
it was real tough, actually.

39:26.729 --> 39:29.729
I needed something,
and I remember, I've...

39:29.731 --> 39:32.765
I've always loved music,
you know?

39:32.767 --> 39:37.104
And I found some songs
that I just...

39:37.106 --> 39:41.441
man, I... I held onto,
you know what I mean?

39:41.443 --> 39:44.977
Like an anchor in a storm.
And they got me through.

39:44.979 --> 39:49.048
And they told me about
a Father in heaven that...

39:49.050 --> 39:50.818
that wanted me.

39:50.820 --> 39:54.655
You know,
a Father that loves me so much

39:54.657 --> 39:57.591
that He died for me.

39:57.593 --> 39:59.425
A Father
that would never leave me.

39:59.427 --> 40:02.062
And I listened to these songs
over and over

40:02.064 --> 40:06.466
and over and over again and...
and they gave me hope.

40:06.468 --> 40:09.470
'Cause I needed it.

40:09.472 --> 40:12.138
And maybe tonight, so do you.

40:12.140 --> 40:14.608
Sing this with me.

40:14.610 --> 40:16.876
<i>♪ Oh, Lord ♪</i>

40:16.878 --> 40:19.748
<i>♪ You're beautiful ♪</i>

40:22.550 --> 40:24.651
<i>♪ Your face ♪</i>

40:24.653 --> 40:27.991
<i>♪ Is all I seek ♪</i>

40:29.892 --> 40:33.827
<i>♪ For when Your eyes ♪</i>

40:33.829 --> 40:37.664
<i>♪ Are on this child ♪</i>

40:37.666 --> 40:42.671
<i>♪ Your grace abounds to me ♪</i>

40:45.039 --> 40:49.945
<i>♪ Oh, Lord,
please light the fire ♪</i>

40:52.914 --> 40:54.580
<i>♪ That once ♪</i>

40:54.582 --> 40:59.952
<i>♪ Burned bright and clear ♪</i>

40:59.954 --> 41:03.890
<i>♪ Replace the lamp ♪</i>

41:03.892 --> 41:07.528
<i>♪ Of my first love ♪</i>

41:07.530 --> 41:12.901
<i>♪ That burns with holy fear ♪</i>

41:15.470 --> 41:19.909
<i>♪ Oh, Lord,
you're beautiful ♪</i>

41:22.711 --> 41:27.817
<i>♪ Your face is all I seek ♪</i>

41:30.084 --> 41:33.986
<i>♪ For when your eyes ♪</i>

41:33.988 --> 41:37.724
<i>♪ Are on this child ♪</i>

41:37.726 --> 41:43.032
<i>♪ Your grace abounds to me ♪</i>

41:53.142 --> 41:57.144
Thanks for coming.
Hey, Bart.

41:57.146 --> 42:00.113
- Hey, where you headed, man?
- Someone I gotta see, man.

42:00.115 --> 42:01.914
- Who?
- Scott Brickell.

42:01.916 --> 42:04.483
He manages Audio Adrenaline
and a bunch of others.

42:04.485 --> 42:06.919
- Yeah, well, why was he here?
- 'Cause I wrote him a letter

42:06.921 --> 42:08.754
every week
for the past two years.

42:08.756 --> 42:10.126
- Gotta go.
- Uh...

42:13.595 --> 42:17.030
- Mr. Brickell!
- It's just Brickell.

42:17.032 --> 42:19.265
Uh, yeah, uh-huh, okay.

42:19.267 --> 42:22.836
Um, I didn't know
you were coming. Thank you.

42:22.838 --> 42:24.671
Yeah, well, I did.
Merry Christmas.

42:24.673 --> 42:28.075
Uh, you know, we mostly
just play, uh, big shows,

42:28.077 --> 42:31.111
you know, but sometimes
we like to get back to,

42:31.113 --> 42:32.979
you know,
smaller venues like this one.

42:32.981 --> 42:36.015
- Yeah, look, Barth, uh...
- Uh, it's Bart.

42:36.017 --> 42:38.619
Sorry. And what's the name
of your band again?

42:38.621 --> 42:41.888
It's MercyMe, you know,
'cause when I told my memaw

42:41.890 --> 42:43.756
that we were starting a band,
she was, like,

42:43.758 --> 42:45.725
"Mercy me, get a real job."

42:45.727 --> 42:47.628
And I was, like,
"Aw, Memaw!"

42:47.630 --> 42:49.829
And then the guys were like,
"Did she really say that?"

42:49.831 --> 42:52.633
I was, like, "Yeah, we
have to name the band Mercy..."

42:52.635 --> 42:55.202
So that's what we called it.

42:55.204 --> 42:57.303
Son,
the sheer volume of words

42:57.305 --> 43:00.742
that comes outta your mouth
is... exhausting.

43:03.945 --> 43:07.180
You're not ready.
That's what I think.

43:07.182 --> 43:09.716
You got talent.
You got potential.

43:09.718 --> 43:13.921
You can sing, but I don't
you've found your song,

43:13.923 --> 43:15.625
Found your soul,
you know what I'm saying?

43:18.660 --> 43:23.095
Look, that last thing you did,
that was... that was special.

43:23.097 --> 43:26.800
Next gig, you should do that
the whole time, the entire show.

43:26.802 --> 43:28.635
See how that works for you.

43:28.637 --> 43:30.704
That's not the kind of music
that we sing, though.

43:30.706 --> 43:33.240
Trust me, son, you have no idea
what kind of music you sing.

43:33.242 --> 43:35.309
We write our own music.
We don't just do covers.

43:35.311 --> 43:37.678
Well, then write
something like that,

43:37.680 --> 43:39.345
- and then give me a call.
- No, no, no. Wait, wait, wait.

43:39.347 --> 43:42.615
You gotta go with us.
We got two more shows in Texas.

43:42.617 --> 43:45.151
We got plenty of room
on the bus, all right?

43:45.153 --> 43:46.887
You know, you can't just
change up our whole act

43:46.889 --> 43:48.722
and then abandon us, right?

43:48.724 --> 43:52.593
You don't seem like that
kind of person, I can tell.

43:52.595 --> 43:55.662
I flew coach
in a middle seat

43:55.664 --> 43:59.032
to rent a car
that I can't even fit in

43:59.034 --> 44:01.702
to drive three hours
to the middle of nowhere

44:01.704 --> 44:06.707
to have you tell me you want me
to travel on <i>that...</i>

44:06.709 --> 44:07.911
with you?

44:10.244 --> 44:11.678
Yeah.

44:17.251 --> 44:19.655
That's funny.

44:21.055 --> 44:22.958
I need to get another job.

44:34.168 --> 44:35.401
<i>Hello?</i>

44:35.403 --> 44:37.037
Yes, is this Shannon Street?

44:37.039 --> 44:39.106
<i>Yes. Who is this?</i>

44:39.108 --> 44:41.707
Uh, it's the police, ma'am.
Uh, we need to speak with you.

44:41.709 --> 44:44.646
Can you come downstairs?
It's for your own safety.

44:49.751 --> 44:52.121
Get the girl, Bart!
Woo-woo!

44:56.758 --> 44:59.325
- Shannon!
- Bart!

44:59.327 --> 45:03.162
Hey. Long time no see.
You look great.

45:03.164 --> 45:04.830
It's midnight, Bart.
What are you doing here?

45:04.832 --> 45:06.365
We just played a gig here.

45:06.367 --> 45:08.300
I don't know
if you know this yet, but we...

45:08.302 --> 45:11.037
we actually have a CD now
with actual songs on it.

45:11.039 --> 45:14.341
Like a real CD.
Here, that's for you.

45:14.343 --> 45:17.778
We have three more shows.
What if you came with us?

45:17.780 --> 45:19.245
We could go on the road,
we could grab Kent.

45:19.247 --> 45:20.946
Hit the road.
It'd be like before.

45:20.948 --> 45:23.783
Three Musketeers.
I'm going to bed.

45:23.785 --> 45:26.986
Aw, come on, Shannon.
Go on an adventure!

45:26.988 --> 45:28.320
It'll be fun!

45:28.322 --> 45:30.724
Adventure?

45:30.726 --> 45:32.258
- Really?
- Yeah.

45:32.260 --> 45:34.794
What're you thinking,
coming here like this?

45:34.796 --> 45:36.796
I don't know.
I didn't really think about it.

45:36.798 --> 45:38.265
I just thought
it'd be fun, you know?

45:38.267 --> 45:42.202
- Just an idea.
- That's it? Only reason?

45:42.204 --> 45:44.805
Yep.

45:44.807 --> 45:47.744
I don't want to go on
any more adventures with you.

45:54.115 --> 45:55.448
You know,
I want you to know

45:55.450 --> 45:57.818
that I pray for you
all the time.

45:57.820 --> 46:00.820
I do. I really do.

46:00.822 --> 46:02.823
And I hope that you find

46:02.825 --> 46:05.892
whatever it is that
you're looking for out there.

46:05.894 --> 46:07.830
Thank you for the CD.

46:11.133 --> 46:13.269
Forrest Gump's taking
his time back there.

46:15.369 --> 46:17.204
She will not be joining us.

46:17.206 --> 46:19.773
Shocker.

46:19.775 --> 46:21.977
Well,
ain't <i>she</i> the smart one?

46:50.773 --> 46:53.475
- It's good.
- Nathan, it's real good.

46:56.177 --> 46:59.281
Let's do it.
Let's blow him away.

47:01.349 --> 47:04.117
<i>♪ From the top of the world ♪</i>

47:04.119 --> 47:06.186
<i>♪ I will sing ♪</i>

47:06.188 --> 47:08.954
<i>♪ Of the joy that flows ♪</i>

47:08.956 --> 47:12.392
<i>♪ From my glorious king ♪</i>

47:12.394 --> 47:16.028
<i>♪ And in my heart, Lord ♪</i>

47:16.030 --> 47:18.430
<i>♪ I can see ♪</i>

47:18.432 --> 47:21.401
<i>♪ Your loving arms ♪</i>

47:21.403 --> 47:25.305
<i>♪ Coming down to me ♪</i>

47:25.307 --> 47:27.908
<i>♪ By your blood ♪</i>

47:27.910 --> 47:31.912
<i>♪ That washed over me ♪</i>

47:31.914 --> 47:33.914
<i>♪ By your grace ♪</i>

47:33.916 --> 47:37.316
<i>♪ That came down
and kissed me ♪</i>

47:37.318 --> 47:40.352
<i>♪ Jesus you
have cleaned my heart ♪</i>

47:40.354 --> 47:42.189
<i>♪ And my soul ♪</i>

47:42.191 --> 47:45.925
<i>♪ For your glory,
it made me ♪</i>

47:45.927 --> 47:49.930
<i>♪ Made me beautiful ♪</i>

47:58.941 --> 48:01.207
Hey! Where you going?

48:01.209 --> 48:02.508
Back to Nashville.

48:02.510 --> 48:05.447
I've seen all I need to see.

48:07.548 --> 48:09.615
Plus, I need to make some plans
on account

48:09.617 --> 48:11.885
of booking you guys
a venue for GMA week.

48:11.887 --> 48:14.086
What is GMA week?

48:14.088 --> 48:16.923
- What is that?
- It's only the biggest convention in music...

48:16.925 --> 48:19.358
- Just go on the bus!
- All right.

48:19.360 --> 48:20.994
I couldn't get
the main stage,

48:20.996 --> 48:22.928
but I'll get
some record labels there.

48:22.930 --> 48:26.365
What I need you to do is invite
every youth group you can.

48:26.367 --> 48:27.968
Stack the room.

48:27.970 --> 48:29.568
And then just do
what you did tonight.

48:29.570 --> 48:32.305
Wait.
So you liked tonight?

48:32.307 --> 48:33.910
Don't get cocky, kid.

48:54.997 --> 48:56.629
<i>Hey, this is Shannon.
Leave a message.</i>

48:56.631 --> 49:00.033
Hey, Shannon.

49:00.035 --> 49:02.135
Uh, it's Bart.

49:02.137 --> 49:04.137
Just uh...

49:04.139 --> 49:06.372
look, you said you, uh,
prayed for me

49:06.374 --> 49:08.575
all the time, and I, uh...

49:08.577 --> 49:12.044
we're playing this, uh,
big showcase tomorrow,

49:12.046 --> 49:15.115
and, uh,
it's a big deal for us,

49:15.117 --> 49:17.517
and we just, uh... we're ready.

49:17.519 --> 49:22.191
But we're a...
touch frightened too, um...

49:24.459 --> 49:28.461
I guess that's it.
Just wanted to tell you that.

49:28.463 --> 49:29.463
Uh...

49:52.287 --> 49:54.187
Little off-Broadway,
I know, but it's the best

49:54.189 --> 49:56.055
- I could do on short notice.
- Are you kidding me?

49:56.057 --> 49:57.957
This is perfect.

49:57.959 --> 49:59.959
Oh, and, guys,
this is your sound man, Dingo.

49:59.961 --> 50:02.128
Anything you need,
you just let him know.

50:02.130 --> 50:04.064
You got us a sound guy?

50:04.066 --> 50:06.066
Did you get a label to come?

50:06.068 --> 50:08.068
No.

50:08.070 --> 50:11.271
I got five.
Working on a few more.

50:11.273 --> 50:14.410
I just need you to make sure
this place is full.

50:17.979 --> 50:19.979
And bring the rain,
gentlemen.

50:19.981 --> 50:21.480
- Yeah you got it.
- Absolutely.

50:34.095 --> 50:37.097
Buddy, you ready for this?

50:37.099 --> 50:38.234
Good crowd, huh?

50:40.501 --> 50:43.102
Bart, we've got
a little situation

50:43.104 --> 50:45.106
I need to talk to you about.

50:47.209 --> 50:48.444
Come on.

50:51.546 --> 50:54.013
So, Bart, there's somebody
I want you to meet.

50:54.015 --> 50:55.381
This is a friend of mine.

50:55.383 --> 50:57.117
He came down here tonight
to see us.

50:57.119 --> 50:58.617
- Whoa, Smitty?!
- This is Michael W. Smith.

50:58.619 --> 51:00.754
Smitty, right?

51:00.756 --> 51:02.722
That's what your friends
call you, right?

51:02.724 --> 51:04.557
Yeah, yeah, uh,
nice to meet you.

51:04.559 --> 51:08.561
I am, like, a huge fan
from, like, all the...

51:08.563 --> 51:10.162
- sorry, like,
- That's okay, man.

51:10.164 --> 51:11.664
All the way back.
Way back.

51:11.666 --> 51:14.767
Your tour with was just
so inspiring for me.

51:14.769 --> 51:17.236
I remember you wore
that vest, that red vest!

51:17.238 --> 51:20.140
- Dude, that was bold.
- I don't think I wore a red vest.

51:20.142 --> 51:21.573
- I would buy that vest.
- No, you did.

51:21.575 --> 51:23.809
You wore this red vest.
You remember?

51:23.811 --> 51:26.379
Di... did I wear a red vest
on our tour?

51:26.381 --> 51:27.546
- He did.
- Yes, you did.

51:27.548 --> 51:29.816
It was velvet.

51:29.818 --> 51:31.617
Oh, man.

51:31.619 --> 51:33.318
What?

51:33.320 --> 51:36.391
Miss Bart, I'm...
oh, we're... okay.

51:40.162 --> 51:41.564
Uh...

51:43.432 --> 51:45.698
- You okay?
- I just threw up a little bit.

51:45.700 --> 51:49.068
Yeah. No, I'm good.
I just... you are like...

51:49.070 --> 51:52.137
The first Christian tape
I ever got was "Never Alone."

51:52.139 --> 51:56.376
And it was like...
like an anchor for me.

51:56.378 --> 51:58.178
Thank you so much.
That means so much to me.

51:58.180 --> 52:00.613
Yeah, it was just...
It was... it was great.

52:00.615 --> 52:02.215
There you are.

52:02.217 --> 52:04.117
We're just so excited
to cheer you on.

52:04.119 --> 52:05.785
- Here's Wonder Woman!
- Go get him, please.

52:05.787 --> 52:07.720
Here's Amy Grant!
You are like a super hero...

52:07.722 --> 52:09.823
- We gotta roll. Sorry.
- What, we're hanging out.

52:09.825 --> 52:11.791
- Hi, guys.
- This is Mike.

52:11.793 --> 52:15.494
- Hey. Good luck, Bart.
- Yeah, good... have a good one.

52:15.496 --> 52:17.530
- Did you see who that was?
- I did.

52:17.532 --> 52:20.200
That was Amy Grant.
She talked to me.

52:39.354 --> 52:42.555
Come on, Nashvi-i-lle!

52:42.557 --> 52:45.557
Whoo! What's up GMA?

52:45.559 --> 52:47.762
Are you guys ready
to rock tonight?

52:50.865 --> 52:54.200
Man, we are so glad
to be here with you!

52:54.202 --> 52:56.769
Ever feel like everything
in your life

52:56.771 --> 53:00.907
is just building and building
and building to one big moment?

53:00.909 --> 53:04.313
That's how we feel tonight!
Let's do this!

53:17.358 --> 53:19.427
Whoo!

53:23.664 --> 53:27.367
Bart.
You're stressing me out, man.

53:27.369 --> 53:31.637
Sorry.
It's nerves, you know.

53:31.639 --> 53:33.741
I wish they'd hurry up.

53:35.943 --> 53:37.843
I thought it was good, right?
It felt good.

53:37.845 --> 53:39.812
- It was good.
- It was good, man.

53:39.814 --> 53:42.418
- Best show we ever played.
- Crowd was into it, man.

53:44.519 --> 53:46.753
- I'm gonna go talk to them.
- No! Hey! Hey!

53:46.755 --> 53:49.454
- Don't do that, Bart!
- Brickell's got it.

53:49.456 --> 53:51.457
Let him do his job.

53:51.459 --> 53:53.629
What if he can't?

54:00.501 --> 54:02.234
- Hey!
- Wait! Wait!

54:02.236 --> 54:04.303
- Dude, no!
- That's a mistake.

54:04.305 --> 54:06.705
But if you could see
how far they've come from

54:06.707 --> 54:09.575
- the first time I saw 'em...
- Hey! Hey, guys!

54:09.577 --> 54:12.711
Gentlemen.
Oh, and also lady.

54:12.713 --> 54:14.646
- So you guys know Bart?
- Nice to meet y'all.

54:14.648 --> 54:16.249
- Thanks for coming out tonight.
- And I've been getting

54:16.251 --> 54:18.218
some good feedback
from these guys,

54:18.220 --> 54:20.653
- and I'm almost finished...
- Was that awesome or what?

54:20.655 --> 54:22.689
- Don't y'all agree?
- I think we're pretty much finished up here anyway.

54:22.691 --> 54:25.325
Ah, come on,
I wanna know what you think!

54:25.327 --> 54:28.296
- Let me, let me finish up here...
- I want to know what they think.

54:38.340 --> 54:39.805
You really wanna know?

54:39.807 --> 54:43.242
Yeah, I do!
Come on, lay it on me.

54:43.244 --> 54:44.943
Give me all you got,
Mr. Music Man.

54:44.945 --> 54:48.780
- I have the skin of a rhino.
- All I got, okay.

54:48.782 --> 54:51.584
I'm sorry to have to be
the one tell you this, kid,

54:51.586 --> 54:56.356
but, um...
you're just not good enough.

54:56.358 --> 54:57.789
Not yet, anyway.

54:57.791 --> 55:01.827
What? You're wrong.

55:01.829 --> 55:04.963
Seventh graders at youth camp,
that's one thing, Bart.

55:04.965 --> 55:06.899
But this,
this is about record sales.

55:06.901 --> 55:08.635
And I just can't sell
what you're doing up there.

55:08.637 --> 55:10.903
Seventh gr...
we packed the house, man.

55:10.905 --> 55:12.872
We've been selling our
own albums for years now.

55:12.874 --> 55:16.642
I mean, what... what world
are you guys living in?

55:16.644 --> 55:18.246
Reality.

55:19.881 --> 55:22.347
Look, you need to embrace
reality, Bart.

55:22.349 --> 55:24.316
Your stuff...

55:24.318 --> 55:27.887
You're not good enough, Bart.
Dreams don't pay the bills.

55:27.889 --> 55:30.657
All it does...

55:30.659 --> 55:34.394
is keep you from all this...

55:34.396 --> 55:37.062
from knowing what's real.

55:37.064 --> 55:38.731
What about the stuff
we played at the end?

55:38.733 --> 55:40.498
The worship music?

55:40.501 --> 55:42.001
Oh, it was beautiful,
magical, truly.

55:42.003 --> 55:43.535
I've got a brother-in-law
in Denver.

55:43.537 --> 55:45.338
He's looking for
a worship pastor.

55:45.340 --> 55:47.407
- I could put you two together.
- Is she serious?

55:47.409 --> 55:49.975
It's the truth you're mad at,
not me.

55:49.977 --> 55:52.412
My high school football team,
there were a couple of guys

55:52.414 --> 55:55.381
that were good enough to make
a big noise in a small town.

55:55.383 --> 55:57.082
<i>But that was it.
You know what?</i>

55:57.084 --> 55:59.651
<i>They're still there.
They're stuck.</i>

55:59.653 --> 56:01.820
<i>And that's what'll happen
to you.</i>

56:01.822 --> 56:03.756
- You gotta be good at something we can sell.
- Just stop!

56:03.758 --> 56:05.425
Do you guys not get it?
